From c57ef2a6d176223e31905052ae5a768807fa5332 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: thoran <machagadu6@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 20:04:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] refactor(auth): route login/MFA/resend through canonical
 envelope

loginController now uses authOk/authFail/authValidationError so that
login, MFA verify, and resend MFA emit the same envelope as the rest
of the auth lifecycle. Replaces stray res.status().json() blocks for
the 10-attempt brute-force lock and the 4-attempt warning.

Account-not-found responses now mirror the invalid-credentials shape
to prevent enumeration. Successful login returns { user, session: {
accessToken, tokenType } } so refresh/logout can speak the same
session shape.
